  "prompt": "Is Real Life Springtrap real?",
  "response": "\"Real Life Springtrap\" refers to the character Springtrap from the \"Five Nights at Freddy's\" horror video game series created by Scott Cawthon. In the games, Springtrap is an animatronic possessed by the spirit of the murderer William Afton.\n\nSpringtrap, as depicted in the game and associated media, is purely a fictional character. However, there are many fan creations, costumes, and replicas that people make to bring Springtrap to life in physical form, especially around Halloween or at conventions. These physical recreations can appear very realistic but they are not \"real\" in the sense of having any autonomous or supernatural qualities; they are simply representations of the character made for entertainment and artistic purposes.",
